snippet.textDisplay: I think we're seeing the end of the team that Pochettino created. Age, tired legs, but also an 'aversion' to Mourinho's methods and style of football are now accelerating this. Expect some big names to go in the summer. I think we know who these will be. No, not Kane but others who've been in the news recently. At this moment it's difficult to see Tottenham playing in the CL next season. RB Leipzig were all over them from start to finish. Quicker, better, hungirer, and more motivated. Did Spurs fans REALLY think that their team would win in Leipzig and knock RB out, given their (Spurs)  indifferent form?  more alarmingly, did the Spurs players think they would despite too many Spurs players being off form right now.
